# Frontend — ELD Trip Planner

Senior React standards for this repo. **Current stack:** React 19, Vite, Tailwind, TypeScript (`.tsx`/`.ts`), Jest + RTL, raw `fetch` in `lib/api.ts`. **Target stack** (adopt incrementally): TanStack Query, Zustand, React Hook Form, shadcn/ui.

## Style

- Direct and concise; no comments unless logic is non-obvious
- Single quotes for strings; 2-space indent; no trailing whitespace
- Prefer `const`; use `??` and optional chaining over `||` when empty string matters

## Folder structure

```
frontend/src/
  app/              # App shell, layout, providers (App.tsx, main.tsx)
  features/         # Feature modules (e.g. trip-planner/)
    trip-planner/
      components/   # Feature-only UI
      hooks/        # Feature data + form hooks
      api/          # Feature API calls
      types/        # TS types or JSDoc typedefs
  components/       # Shared UI only (AddressAutocomplete, ErrorBoundary)
  lib/              # Pure utilities (route math, formatters)
  hooks/            # Shared hooks
  styles/           # Global CSS only
```

- One folder per component: `ComponentName/ComponentName.tsx`, `index.ts`, optional `ComponentName.test.tsx`, optional `ComponentName.module.css`
- **Do not** put feature logic in `App.tsx` — extract layout, empty state, and data hooks
- **Do not** mix canvas/math/rendering in one 200+ line file — extract pure functions to `lib/` or `*.utils.ts`

## Components

- **Functional components + hooks only** — no class components
- Error boundaries: use `react-error-boundary` via `components/ErrorBoundary/ErrorBoundary.tsx` (function wrapper + `FallbackComponent`)
- Named exports for utilities; default export for the main component in each folder
- Import order: React → third-party → `@/` or `lib/` → relative
- Props: TypeScript interfaces in `types/` or colocated with the component
- Composition over prop drilling; custom hooks for reusable stateful logic
- Error boundaries around result panels that depend on API shape

## State & data

| Concern | Current | Target |
|--------|---------|--------|
| Server data (plan trip, suggest) | `lib/api.ts` + `useState` in hooks | TanStack Query (`useQuery` / `useMutation`) |
| Form state | Local state in TripForm | React Hook Form |
| Global UI state | Lifted to App | Zustand slice if shared across features |
| URL state | N/A (single page) | React Router when routes are added |

- API calls live in `features/*/api/` or `lib/api.ts`, never inside presentational components
- Handle loading, error, and empty states explicitly; user-facing messages only (no stack traces)

## Styling

- Tailwind utility classes; mobile-first responsive breakpoints
- Shared field styles via `@layer components` in `index.css` (`.field-label`, `.field-input`)
- No inline `style={{}}` except dynamic values (map marker colors, canvas)
- shadcn/ui + Radix when adding new primitives — copy into `components/ui/`, don't npm-install the package

## Performance

- `useMemo` / `useCallback` only when profiling or eslint requires it (stable deps for geometry, cumulative routes)
- Side effects in `useEffect`, never in `useMemo`
- `React.lazy` + `Suspense` for heavy routes (MapView + Leaflet) when bundle size matters
- Debounce + abort autocomplete requests (see AddressAutocomplete)

## Testing

- Colocate: `ComponentName.test.tsx` next to the component
- Jest + React Testing Library (current); Vitest is acceptable when migrating
- Test behavior and accessibility roles, not implementation details
- Mock `lib/api` at module boundary, not `fetch` globally

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML (`form`, `label`, `button`, `ul`/`li` for lists)
- Combobox pattern: `role="combobox"`, `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`, `listbox`/`option`
- Canvas: `aria-label` describing the log day
- Keyboard: autocomplete supports ↑/↓, Enter, Escape

## Security

- Never inject user/API strings into `innerHTML` or Leaflet `html` templates without escaping
- Validate inputs client-side; server remains source of truth

## Anti-patterns (fix when touching the file)

```jsx
// BAD — god App with fetch, layout, and sub-views
export default function App() {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null);
  async function handleSubmit() { /* fetch */ }
  return (/* 150 lines */);
}

// GOOD — thin App, feature hook, colocated views
export default function App() {
  const trip = useTripPlanner();
  return <TripPlannerLayout {...trip} />;
}
```

```jsx
// BAD — side effect in useMemo
useMemo(() => map.fitBounds(points), [map, points]);

// GOOD
useEffect(() => { map.fitBounds(points); }, [map, points]);
```

```jsx
// BAD — 200 lines of canvas math inside the component file
function drawSheet(canvas, log) { /* ... */ }

// GOOD — lib/log-sheet-draw.ts (pure) + thin LogSheet.tsx
```

## File naming

- Components: PascalCase folder + file (`TripForm/TripForm.tsx`)
- Utilities/hooks: camelCase (`useTripPlanner.ts`, `formatClock.ts`)
- Tests: `*.test.tsx` beside source
